headline: Constellation Energy Deepens Data Center Ties With Calpine Deal And Nuclear Upgrades
summary: Constellation Energy (NasdaqGS:CEG) completed a US$26.6b acquisition of Calpine, expanding its generation footprint and customer reach. The company signed a long term 380 MW power supply agreement with data center developer CyrusOne targeting large scale facilities. Regulators approved upgrades at key nuclear facilities, clearing the way for higher capacity and reliability from carbon free assets.
